Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper uses mathematical models and simulations to predict the confirmation time of Bitcoin transactions. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the probabilistic distribution of Bitcoin transactions, which can be seen as a form of information. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the queueing process of Bitcoin transactions, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper models the confirmation time of Bitcoin transactions as a stochastic fluid queueing process, which can be seen as a control system. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper deals with Bitcoin transactions, which are based on cryptography and have security implications.
